 family has made it abundently clear they would prefer me to stay in the normal paths of choice, but I must answer the call of Prexus.<br><br>Regardless I wish to say hello and introduce myself to the comunity outside my little perfect corner of Norrath.  Hopefully I will meet some of you in our adventures.<br><br>- Lazurith of Odus<br><br>(OOC Hey all, I am a old-time EQer who still plays on Morell-Thull but was part of the crew who helped test FV last year.  My guild (The Champions of the Light) is one of a few RP servers there.  I was part of the large movement to MT to make it the 'Players Role-Play Server' and even though it is a great server...well as with all large and established ones it is crouded and ull of non-roleplayers...and a uber guild or two. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Anyhow I hope to find a strong role-play comunity here on Firiona Vie and hopefully forge some strong friendships like I have on Morell Thull.<br><br>- D) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umahakala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mahakala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 12:52:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1197.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hail and well met all!</span><hr size=1> Lazurith,<br><br>Welcome aboard!  I played on Morell Thule as well prior to coming here.  I have been on FV for a little over a week now and I must say it is the most enjoyable EQ experience I have had since my first 6 months.  The change in pace took me a few days to get use to, but now I wouldn't change it for the world.  Almost everyone I have encountered is friendly and &quot;mature&quot;.  Much like the early days on Morell.  Enjoy your stay and feel free to ask me any questions that you might have.  Mahakala is currently residing in his home town of Qeynos, stop in and say &quot;Hello&quot; some afternoon.  Best of luck and well met friend!<br><br>-Maha <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 1:14:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1197.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/hand.gif height=42 width=42></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hail and well met all!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> /ooc</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>Heh.  I tried Morell-Thule for a while when I heard it was an &quot;unofficial roleplay server&quot; of sorts, but my experiences indicated that it'd be more accurately described as the &quot;don't speak English server.&quot; ;)<br><br>Anyway, welcome aboard.  I pesonally have noticed more erudite paladins on this server than on the others, but they are still a rarity.  What I am finding is that there are actually a pretty solid number of erudite clerics, which is kind of interesting.  I can only remember encountering a couple of those on other servers.<br><br>I hope you find what you're looking for on FV and have a good time. :) <p><B><FONT FACE="Comic Sans MS">--Tukka</FONT></B><BR>Player of Velsor Secarne (on Firiona Vie)<BR>Shadow Knight of Cazic-Thule<BR>Seeker of the Dark Truth<BR>Officer of the <A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/theindigovoid">Indigo Void</A><BR>Fluent in Human, Erudite, Teir'Dal, Elvish, Halfling, Ogre and Lizardman</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolo